   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO TO OVERCOME THE LEAVING OF THE FIRST LOVE Scripture Reading: Rev 2:1-7; 12:17b; 20:4, 6; 1 John 4:8, 16; John 3:16; 1 John 4:9; Rom 5:5; 2 Cor 13:14; Eph 2:4-5; John 1:12-13; 3:3-6, 29-30; Rev 19:7; 21:2, 7; Eph 5:25; Rev 21:9; Rom 8:35-39; 2 Cor 5:14-15; Rom 14:7-9; Rev 2:10; 12:11; 22:17; Jer 2:2; 31:3 OUTLINE In a church: Being orderly and formal Rev 2:2-3.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>But having left the first love v. 4.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>To overcome the leaving of the first love v. 5a: The first love the best love: The love which is God Himself 1 John 4:8, 16: To give His only begotten Son to us as our portion John 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>To send His Son into the world that we might have life and live through Him 1 John 4:9.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To be poured out in our hearts through the Holy Spirit Rom 5:5.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To be the source for our enjoyment of the dispensing of the Triune God 2 Cor 13:14.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>As the Father's love in life to regenerate us that we may become His children Eph 2:4-5; John 1:12-13.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God's regenerated children become the members of Christ to constitute the Body of Christ, the bride of Christ, as His increase for Him to love John 3:3-6, 29-30; Rev 19:7; 21:2, 7.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Christ as the Husband loves the church as His wife with the Father's love as the love of affection Eph 5:25; Rev 21:9; Rom 8:35, 39: Christ's love of affection constrains us to live and to die for Him 2 Cor 5:14-15; Rom 14:7-9.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Christ's love makes the believers martyrs for Him Rev 2:10; 12:11; Rom 8:35-37.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To recover the first love is to recover the bridal love, the eternal love, for the Lord Rev 22:17; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Jer 2:2; 31:3.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To repent and do the first works.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To maintain the eating of Christ as the tree of life Rev 2:7: To continue the enjoyment of the life supply of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>In the present church life of the Paradise of God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To shine forth the divine light as the lampstand cf. v. 5b: Corporately versus individualistically.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In the dark night of the church age.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To keep the testimony of Jesus as the shining of the lampstand in their locality Rev 12:17b: Testifying Christ's person as God and as man.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Testifying Christ's human living, crucifixion, resurrection, ascension, descension, and second appearing.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In our daily life.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To be rewarded Rev 2:7: To participate in full in the enjoyment of the rich life supply of Christ as the embodiment of the processed and consummated Triune God.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In the New Jerusalem in its freshness as the Paradise of God for one thousand years Rev 20:4, 6.</S>
   </TEXT>
